## PDRA position

The PDRA position is intended for candidates with expertise in applied and computational mathematics, with fluid mechanics being highly desirable. Experience in scientific computing and in numerical methods for partial differential equations, including finite element and/or boundary element methods, will also be advantageous.

The postdoctoral researcher will help develop mathematical and computational models for electrically driven helical microswimmers and related active matter systems, with scope to contribute both analytically and computationally. The successful candidate will join an active and supportive research environment and contribute to internationally relevant work in modern mathematical modelling.

### Essential information

- The position is available for **two years in the first instance**, with the possibility of extension to a total of **three years**, subject to satisfactory performance.
- Applicants should be educated to a minimum of **PhD level in an appropriate discipline**, or have significant relevant experience in addition to a relevant degree.
- Applications are also welcome from candidates who are **close to PhD completion or whose award is pending**. In such cases, the appointment will initially be made at **Research Assistant level (grade 6)** until the PhD award is confirmed.
- The role is particularly suited to applicants with a strong background in **applied mathematics**, with expertise in **fluid mechanics** highly desirable.
- Experience in **scientific computing**, **numerical methods for PDEs**, and especially **finite element and/or boundary element methods** will be advantageous.

